-- NTT Data to Acquire U.S. IT Firm Keane for $1.23 Billion, Nikkei Reports
-- B y   T a k   K u m a k u r a
-- 2010-10-20T22:42:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/ntt-data-to-acquire-u-s-it-firm-keane-for-1-23-billion-nikkei-reports.html
NTT Data Corp. will acquire Keane
Inc., a closely held U.S. technology company, for about 100
billion yen ($1.23 billion), the Nikkei newspaper reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  Tokyo-based NTT Data, a unit of Nippon Telegraph and
Telephone Corp., will purchase all the shares in Boston-based
Keane, which is half-owned by a Citigroup Inc. unit and the rest
by employees, the newspaper said.  The move is part of NTT Dataâ€™s efforts to increase its
overseas sales to 300 billion yen by March 2013, compared with
70 billion yen for fiscal 2009.   The companies seek to reach an agreement by the end of this
month, the report said. NTT Data spokesman Norihiko Sugimoto and
Keane spokeswoman Tara Jantzen declined to comment.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
